Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:04:23.168 --> 02:04:25.251
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:04:39.918 --> 02:04:42.960
Bahu, it is
a time-honoured ritual.

02:04:43.126 --> 02:04:43.960
If you don't
sacrifice the animal

02:04:44.168 --> 02:04:46.251
the soldiers will read it as a bad omen.
- Yes, My Prince!

02:04:46.418 --> 02:04:48.501
If you don't offer the sacrifice

02:04:48.668 --> 02:04:50.001
the Goddess will be angry.

02:04:50.168 --> 02:04:51.835
Why quench the
Goddess's thirst with

02:04:52.043 --> 02:04:53.710
the blood of
this innocent animal

02:04:54.126 --> 02:04:56.501
when my own blood
can be offered?

02:04:59.293 --> 02:05:01.835
Hail Mahishmati!
- Hail Mahishmati!

02:05:02.001 --> 02:05:05.501
Hail Mahishmathi!
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:05:05.668 --> 02:05:07.960
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:05:08.168 --> 02:05:10.251
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:05:10.418 --> 02:05:13.876
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:05:21.793 --> 02:05:23.960
Mahishmathi will be
forgiving and benevolent!

02:05:26.626 --> 02:05:28.126
This is your last chance.

02:05:28.293 --> 02:05:31.585
Drop your weapons and run
and we will spare your lives.

02:05:46.668 --> 02:05:48.626
I heard that you promised
both your sons that

02:05:48.793 --> 02:05:51.335
the one who kills me
would be made king.

02:05:56.793 --> 02:05:59.501
And if both of them
die at my hands?

02:06:16.876 --> 02:06:19.501
I will conquer you
and your kingdom

02:06:19.668 --> 02:06:20.960
and then I will have
a son with you.

02:06:21.126 --> 02:06:22.710
You can make him the king!

02:06:31.626 --> 02:06:33.251
I want him alive.

02:06:34.293 --> 02:06:37.585
I want him to be alive
even after his arms and legs

02:06:37.751 --> 02:06:40.376
are cut off and he
lies in a pool of blood!

02:06:47.293 --> 02:06:52.126
When the vultures pluck out
his eyes and feast on his guts.

02:06:52.793 --> 02:06:54.751
He should be alive.

02:06:56.251 --> 02:06:58.085
Kattappa!
<i>'</i> My Lady!

02:06:58.251 --> 02:07:00.335
Blow the conch
to begin the battle.

02:07:31.501 --> 02:07:32.751
It is ready.

02:07:32.918 --> 02:07:33.835
Arm the weapon.

02:07:39.626 --> 02:07:40.876
Fire!

02:07:46.793 --> 02:07:48.335
Baahubali's command!

02:08:15.918 --> 02:08:17.001
Get ready!

02:08:18.376 --> 02:08:20.210
Arm the weapons.

02:09:27.168 --> 02:09:28.335
Attack!

02:10:27.251 --> 02:10:29.376
Attack!

02:12:10.043 --> 02:12:12.835
Well done, Baahubali!
- Well done.

02:12:42.293 --> 02:12:44.251
Soldiers. Attack.

02:12:44.418 --> 02:12:45.960
Attack!

02:13:05.168 --> 02:13:07.751
Hold! Hold strong!

02:13:23.918 --> 02:13:25.751
Swords group, step forward!

02:15:29.918 --> 02:15:32.126
Trident strategy begins!

02:18:01.293 --> 02:18:02.585
Stop.

02:18:08.793 --> 02:18:10.001
Bhallaladeva!

02:18:15.751 --> 02:18:17.001
My Prince?

02:18:28.418 --> 02:18:30.335
My Prince!
- Army!

02:20:02.251 --> 02:20:05.251
Hold your lines!

02:20:13.043 --> 02:20:15.876
Hold your lines! Hold them!

02:20:59.918 --> 02:21:01.876
Our defenses are in tatters.

02:21:02.293 --> 02:21:04.460
We are seeing an enemy
flag on Mahishmati soil...

02:21:04.626 --> 02:21:05.626
for the first time!

02:21:05.793 --> 02:21:08.210
This is the death of us. Death!

02:21:08.793 --> 02:21:11.460
Death! Death!

02:22:01.876 --> 02:22:03.126
Death!

02:22:06.418 --> 02:22:07.835
Death!

02:22:11.293 --> 02:22:12.626
Soldiers!

02:22:20.501 --> 02:22:22.085
What is death?

02:22:23.751 --> 02:22:26.085
To think that the
enemy is stronger

02:22:26.251 --> 02:22:27.876
than our resolve, is death!

02:22:29.751 --> 02:22:34.126
Cowardice on the battlefield
is death!

02:22:36.043 --> 02:22:40.501
The cruel man insulted our
mother and he is still alive.

02:22:42.418 --> 02:22:45.501
Instead of presenting his
decapitated head at her feet

02:22:45.668 --> 02:22:48.001
we are turning our backs
to him and that is death!

02:22:53.043 --> 02:22:56.126
I will ride on to annihilate
that death!

02:22:57.251 --> 02:23:01.335
No rogue can ever harm
my mother or my motherland.

02:23:01.543 --> 02:23:05.751
lam about to rip them apart
and proclaim my war cry!

02:23:11.168 --> 02:23:13.251
Who is with me?

02:23:15.293 --> 02:23:16.626
Me!

02:23:16.793 --> 02:23:19.626
Who will die with me?
- Me!

02:23:19.876 --> 02:23:24.626
Who will vanquish that
death and live on? - Me!

02:23:26.376 --> 02:23:27.626
Me!

02:23:27.793 --> 02:23:30.251
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:23:30.418 --> 02:23:32.376
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:23:32.626 --> 02:23:36.751
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:23:47.376 --> 02:23:49.001
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:23:50.543 --> 02:23:54.085
Hail Mahishmathi!

02:24:20.543 --> 02:24:21.751
Sethupathy!

02:29:13.793 --> 02:29:16.085
<i>I want him alive when
the vultures pluck out his eyes</i>

02:29:16.251 --> 02:29:18.751
<i>and feast on his guts.</i>

02:29:19.543 --> 02:29:24.251
<i>His limbs are to be cut off
and his blood should flow!</i>

02:29:48.668 --> 02:29:50.001
MY son!

02:29:51.626 --> 02:29:54.626
Bhallaladeva! Bhallaladeva!

02:30:17.751 --> 02:30:19.126
MY son!

02:30:19.876 --> 02:30:26.251
My brave son killed
Kalakeya and won the battle!

02:30:31.501 --> 02:30:35.501
To the future king,
Bhallaladeva!

02:30:35.668 --> 02:30:39.001
Hail Bhallaladeva!
Hail Bhallaladeva!

02:30:40.501 --> 02:30:42.876
Bhallaladeva's valour
will be told in Mahishmati

02:30:43.043 --> 02:30:45.126
for generations to come!

02:30:45.751 --> 02:30:51.376
Tales of his victory will be
etched on shrines and temples.

02:30:51.918 --> 02:30:54.251
Today, I proclaim
my son Bhallaladeva

02:30:54.418 --> 02:30:57.751
as the commander of the
armed forces of Mahishmathi!

02:31:01.168 --> 02:31:05.126
I proclaim Baahubali
as the King of Mahishmathi!

02:31:13.793 --> 02:31:17.126
Sivagami,
What sort of a decision is this?

02:31:17.293 --> 02:31:22.251
My son, our son,
killed the Kalakeya chief!

02:31:22.418 --> 02:31:24.710
You saw it with your own eyes!

02:31:25.543 --> 02:31:29.085
He has to be the King! Only he!

02:31:29.543 --> 02:31:31.876
The merits of a King
are evaluated not

02:31:32.043 --> 02:31:33.835
by the number
of enemies he has killed

02:31:34.001 --> 02:31:36.501
but by the number of
his own people he has saved.

02:31:37.043 --> 02:31:38.001
During the battle

02:31:38.168 --> 02:31:41.126
Bhallaladeva's focus was
only in vanquishing the enemy.

02:31:41.376 --> 02:31:44.376
Baahubali,
while killing the enemy

02:31:44.543 --> 02:31:47.001
also managed
to save his subjects.

02:31:48.001 --> 02:31:50.876
That is the difference
between a soldier and a king.

02:31:53.168 --> 02:31:56.626
If you kill a hundred men you will
be called a great warrior.

02:31:57.293 --> 02:32:01.626
But if you save one life,
you will be called God!

02:32:05.376 --> 02:32:07.001
So, saving a couple
of common men

02:32:07.168 --> 02:32:08.585
is now the
qualification to rule?

02:32:08.751 --> 02:32:11.126
Baahubali will be
crowned the King of

02:32:11.293 --> 02:32:13.376
Mahishmati on
an auspicious day.

02:32:14.418 --> 02:32:17.876
That is my word
and my word is law!

02:32:22.168 --> 02:32:24.585
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:32:25.168 --> 02:32:27.626
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:32:27.793 --> 02:32:30.001
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:32:30.251 --> 02:32:32.210
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:32:32.376 --> 02:32:36.626
Baahubali!
-Baahubali!

02:32:36.793 --> 02:32:39.960
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:32:40.126 --> 02:32:42.210
Baahubali! Baahubali!

02:32:52.751 --> 02:32:55.001
Amarendra Baahubali!

02:32:56.168 --> 02:32:59.751
Glory to him!

02:33:03.418 --> 02:33:06.626
Amarendra Baahubali!

02:33:07.251 --> 02:33:11.001
Glory to him!

02:33:11.251 --> 02:33:14.376
Glory to him!

02:33:16.626 --> 02:33:19.626
My Shiva is the son
of such a great king!

02:33:20.751 --> 02:33:23.460
We are so glad
to hear about him.

02:33:24.418 --> 02:33:27.626
I wish we can
see the great man once!

02:33:30.168 --> 02:33:31.585
He is no more.

02:33:33.293 --> 02:33:35.126
The saviour is no more!
(That God is no more!)

02:33:42.418 --> 02:33:44.626
You said no enemy
could come near him.

02:33:45.126 --> 02:33:47.376
You said the weapons
were afraid to touch him?

02:33:48.918 --> 02:33:51.001
How did such
a great warrior die?

02:33:52.918 --> 02:33:56.460
More grievous than
the wound of a sword or a spear

02:33:57.376 --> 02:33:59.126
is a stab in the back, Mahendra.

02:33:59.543 --> 02:34:02.251
Who? Who was it?

02:34:05.501 --> 02:34:06.876
That traitor...

02:34:09.126 --> 02:34:10.335
was me!

02:34:27.543 --> 02:34:38.501
"Golden dreams
and great heartache."

02:34:41.376 --> 02:34:51.501
"churn in the depth of the soul
of this river called life."

02:34:52.918 --> 02:35:02.835
"When great mountains
lay in its path."

02:35:04.626 --> 02:35:15.876
"It cuts deep gorges through
the rock to keep flowing!"

02:35:17.168 --> 02:35:33.376
"This unstoppable, inexhaustible
river called life."

02:35:35.126 --> 02:35:41.626
"It is called
the river of life."
